# distributed-deque — agent memory

Read `AGENTS.md` at the repo root for the full, maintained summary.

**Topic rules:** `go-conventions.mdc` (Go files), `memory-patterns.mdc` (`memory/`, `cmd/`). **Learning doc:** `docs/deque-guide.md`.

## What this is

Go library: **deque** with **in-memory doubly-linked list** (`MemoryDeque`: nodes + `head`/`tail` + mutex, O(1) both ends). **Distributed** = **`cmd/queued`** owns the only deque and serves HTTP (`POST /push`, `GET /pop`). Other processes use **curl** or any HTTP client — **no** `remote/` package. Redis is **not** in scope. See `README.md`.

- **Module:** `github.com/williamntlam/distributed-deque`
- **Package name:** `distributeddeque`

## Repository layout (target)

```
errors.go, deque.go
memory/node.go, memory/deque.go, memory/deque_test.go
memory/ring.go (later)
cmd/queued/main.go
```

Doubly-linked list in `memory/` — **not** `list/`, `stream/`, or `remote/`. See README **Repository layout**.

